title: Your gig guide to a great night out in Ipswich
text:
Your gig guide to a great night out in Ipswich 22nd Oct 2015 12:00 PM Updated: 12:27 PM 
FIVE-DAY gig guide to the best entertainment in Ipswich. 

Thursday 
Waghorn Diner/ Jam Night Thursdays, Live music from 7pm, weekly jam night open to all musicians from amateurs to professionals. Begins at 7pm at Hotel Metropole. 
Springlake Hotel, Springfield Lakes Bvd / Thirsty Thursdays Free pool and sausage sizzle. Bikini waitresses from 2pm-5pm. Registration at 6pm to play poker. 
Brothers Leagues Club / Morning Melodies / Dan Schulzeck is performing from 11am in the O Bar. 
Ipswich RSL Club, Lowry St, Nth Ipswich / Live music, Marco will perform live from 11am - 2pm. 

Friday 
Goodna Services Club / Live music from Chi-Chi Duo in the Sky Stage from 8pm-midnight. Free entry. 
Coronation Hotel / Live Music / Just Five perform from 7.30pm. 
Royal Mail Hotel, Goodna / Live music, Rumblefish perform from 7pm-10pm. Free entry, with food and drinks available for purchase. 
Ipswich RSL Club, Lowry St, Nth Ipswich / Live music, 7.45pm-11.45pm. Street Cafe will play music to fill the dance floor. Entry as per RSL policy. 
Brothers Leagues Club / Rob Hackwood Trio will perform from 7.30pm in the O Bar followed by Jericho in the Sports Bar from 9.30pm. 
Springlake Hotel / Retro night / DJ's spinning from 9.30pm -1.30am. 

Saturday 
Goodna Services Club / Live music from the Hot Pursuit Duo in the Sky Stage from 8pm-midnight. Free entry. 
Royal Mail Hotel, Goodna / Live music / The Johnson Stompers perform live from 1pm followed by Bakosfield from 4.30pm. 
Brothers Leagues Club / Live music to be performed by Midnight Rambler in the O Bar at 7.30pm, with No Standing playing at 9.30pm in the Sports Bar. 
Springlake Hotel / Some of Brisbane's best cover bands perform from 9.30pm - 1.30am. 
Commercial Hotel, Redbank / Southern Cross Poker tournament. Free to enter with cash prizes to be won. Registration is at 6pm with the game starting at 7pm. 

Sunday 
Coronation Hotel / Live Music / Tiger Street perform live from 2pm. 
Brothers Leagues Club / Live music / Little Stevie and the Tail Fins are set to perform from 2pm - 6pm in the O Bar. 
Spicers Hidden Vale / Sunday Jazz. Enjoy a jazz duo in the idyllic surrounds of the Spicers Hidden Vale from noon-4pm. Bookings are essential for the served lunch. Phone 1300 179 340. 

Later in the Week 
Brothers Leagues Club / Australian Pro Poker / Monday and Wednesdays from 6pm. Ipswich RSL Club, Lowry St, Nth Ipswich / Every Wednesday / Live music, Country and Western Night, Woody Dean will perform live from 6.30pm - 9.30pm. ipswich gig guide
